ZORRO (1957) starring Guy Williams (Don Diego de la Vega / El Zorro), Gene Sheldon (Bernardo), Henry Calvin (Sgt. Garcia), George J. Lewis (Don Alejandro de la Vega)
Guest star: Gloria Talbott (Moneta) , Everett Sloane (Andres Felipe Basilio), Nestor Paiva (Innkeeper), Robert J. Wilke (Captain Mendoza), Edgar Barrier (Don Cornelio)

2x27. The Man from Spain    (4/9/1959) 
The arrogant Felipe Basilio has been sent by the Spanish government to sell bonds to the local citizens in order to help finance the Spanish war effort. Unreasonable levies are placed on the peons and Sgt Garcia is humiliated by being placed in the town stocks.

2x28. Treasure for the King  (4/16/1959) 
The landowners decide to help support the Spanish government as much as possible so that Basilio and Capitan Mendoza have been able to collect three large chests full of gold which they decide to keep for themselves.

2x29. Exposing the Tyrant   (4/23/1959) 
Basilio plans to remain in Los Angeles as a wealthy man. He tells Garcia that Spanish law forbids citizens to possess items made in countries that are at war with Spain. Those that do will forfeit their entire households.
